{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901917071,"sessionID":"ses_283ffa16affeyiZ24apvNnRQcH","part":{"id":"prt_d7c00b2fa001SBIxCBDo0N5pNl","messageID":"msg_d7c00a719001LiRSeKpN8653Wb","sessionID":"ses_283ffa16affeyiZ24apvNnRQcH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n2: \n3: ## AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n8: | **Language** | Python |\n9: | **Size** | M (Medium) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes to enable deployment of AI agents to Kubernetes using either standard K8s resources (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube-specific `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR). These providers SHALL serve as the deployment abstraction layer for the AgentCube CLI, enabling seamless publishing of agents to diverse Kubernetes environments.\n17: \n18: The dual-provider architecture SHALL:\n19: - Support standard Kubernetes deployments for generic K8s clusters\n20: - Support AgentRuntime CR deployments for AgentCube-enabled clusters\n21: - Provide consistent interfaces for deploy, status, and delete operations\n22: - Handle Kubernetes client initialization with fallback to in-cluster config\n23: - Ensure namespace management and resource lifecycle operations\n24: - Integrate with the CLI's `publish`, `invoke`, and `status` commands\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Scope\n29: \n30: ### In Scope\n31: \n32: 1. **KubernetesProvider — Standard K8s Resources**\n33:    - `deploy_agent()` — Create or update Deployment + NodePort Service\n34:    - `wait_for_deployment_ready()` — Poll for deployment readiness with timeout\n35:    - `get_agent_status()` — Retrieve deployment and service status\n36:    - `delete_agent()` — Remove Deployment and Service resources\n37:    - Support for configurable replicas, node_port, and environment variables\n38:    - Proper handling of entrypoint command/args parsing\n39: \n40: 2. **AgentCubeProvider — AgentRuntime CR**\n41:    - `deploy_agent_runtime()` — Create or update AgentRuntime Custom Resource\n42:    - `get_agent_status()` — Retrieve AgentRuntime CR status\n43:    - `delete_agent()` — Delete AgentRuntime CR\n44:    - Support for readiness probes, workload manager URL, and router URL\n45:    - Environment variable injection for AgentCube components\n46:    - Image pull secrets configuration (default: `default-secret`)\n47:    - Session timeout and max session duration configuration\n48: \n49: 3. **Kubernetes Client Management**\n50:    - Lazy initialization of Kubernetes client\n51:    - Kubeconfig loading with fallback to in-cluster configuration\n52:    - Proper error handling for missing `kubernetes` Python library\n53:    - Namespace existence verification and auto-creation\n54:    - Support for both `AppsV1Api` and `CustomObjectsApi`\n55: \n56: 4. **Resource Specification Building**\n57:    - `_create_or_update_deployment()` — Build Deployment spec\n58:    - `_create_or_update_service()` — Build NodePort Service spec\n59:    - `_build_agent_runtime_spec()` — Build AgentRuntime CR spec\n60:    - `_apply_agent_runtime_cr()` — Apply CR via CustomObjectsApi\n61:    - Label-based selector consistency across resources\n62: \n63: 5. **Configuration Handling**\n64:    - Namespace configuration (default: `default`)\n65:    - Image URL and port configuration\n66:    - Entrypoint parsing (command + args split)\n67:    - Environment variable dictionary support\n68:    - Optional NodePort assignment (30000-32767 range validation)\n69:    - Replica count configuration\n70: \n71: 6. **Error Handling & Logging**\n72:    - Structured logging via `self.logger`\n73:    - `RuntimeError` for K8s client initialization failures\n74:    - `ValueError` for invalid node_port or missing required URLs\n75:    - `TimeoutError` for deployment readiness timeout\n76:    - Graceful handling of NotFoundException for idempotent deletes\n77: \n78: ### Out of Scope\n79: \n80: 1. **Helm Chart Support**: No Helm packaging or templating\n81: 2. **Operator Development**: Not building an actual K8s operator, just a client\n82: 3. **Multi-Cluster Management**: Single cluster context per provider instance\n83: 4. **RBAC Management**: No role or service account creation\n84: 5. **Ingress Configuration**: No Ingress or Gateway API resources\n85: 6. **HPA/VPA**: No horizontal or vertical pod autoscaler setup\n86: 7. **Pod Disruption Budgets**: No PDB resource management\n87: 8. **Network Policies**: No network policy configuration\n88: 9. **StatefulSet Support**: Only Deployment-based workloads\n89: 10. **Custom Webhook Handling**: No admission webhook management\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## Design\n94: \n95: ### Provider Class Hierarchy\n96: \n97: ```\n98: ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n99: │     Abstract Deployment Pattern     │\n100: ├─────────────────────────────────────┤\n101: │ + deploy()                          │\n102: │ + get_status()                      │\n103: │ + delete()                          │\n104: └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n105:                │\n106:        ┌───────┴───────┐\n107:        ▼               ▼\n108: ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n109: │ Kubernetes   │  │ AgentCube        │\n110: │ Provider     │  │ Provider         │\n111: ├──────────────┤  ├──────────────────┤\n112: │ Deployment   │  │ AgentRuntime CR  │\n113: │ + Service    │  ├──────────────────┤\n114: ├──────────────┤  │ - router_url     │\n115: │ - namespace  │  │ - workload_mgr   │\n116: │ - replicas   │  │ - readinessProbe │\n117: │ - node_port  │  │ - imagePullSecrets│\n118: └──────────────┘  └──────────────────┘\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### KubernetesProvider Structure\n122: \n123: ```python\n124: class KubernetesProvider:\n125:     def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n126:     \"\"\"Initialize with namespace and verbosity settings.\"\"\"\n127: \n128:     def _get_k8s_client(self) -> Any: ...\n129:     \"\"\"Lazy-load Kubernetes client with config fallback.\"\"\"\n130: \n131:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n132:     \"\"\"Create namespace if it doesn't exist.\"\"\"\n133: \n134:     def deploy_agent(\n135:         self,\n136:         agent_name: str,\n137:         image_url: str,\n138:         port: int,\n139:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n140:         replicas: int = 1,\n141:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n142:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n143:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n144:     \"\"\"Deploy as Deployment + NodePort Service.\"\"\"\n145: \n146:     def _create_or_update_deployment(...) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n147:     \"\"\"Build and apply Deployment resource.\"\"\"\n148: \n149:     def _create_or_update_service(...) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n150:     \"\"\"Build and apply NodePort Service resource.\"\"\"\n151: \n152:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(\n153:         self, name: str, timeout: int = 120, interval: int = 5\n154:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n155:     \"\"\"Poll deployment status until ready or timeout.\"\"\"\n156: \n157:     def get_agent_status(self, name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n158:     \"\"\"Get deployment and service status.\"\"\"\n159: \n160:     def delete_agent(self, name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n161:     \"\"\"Delete deployment and service resources.\"\"\"\n162: ```\n163: \n164: ### AgentCubeProvider Structure\n165: \n166: ```python\n167: class AgentCubeProvider:\n168:     def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n169:     \"\"\"Initialize AgentCube-specific provider.\"\"\"\n170: \n171:     def _get_k8s_client(self) -> Any: ...\n172:     \"\"\"Lazy-load Kubernetes client.\"\"\"\n173: \n174:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n175:     \"\"\"Ensure namespace exists.\"\"\"\n176: \n177:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n178:         self,\n179:         agent_name: str,\n180:         image_url: str,\n181:         port: int,\n182:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n183:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n184:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n185:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n186:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n187:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n188:         session_timeout: str = \"15m\",\n189:         max_session_duration: str = \"8h\",\n190:         image_pull_secrets: Optional[list] = None,\n191:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n192:     \"\"\"Deploy AgentRuntime Custom Resource.\"\"\"\n193: \n194:     def _build_agent_runtime_spec(...) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n195:     \"\"\"Build AgentRuntime CR specification dictionary.\"\"\"\n196: \n197:     def _apply_agent_runtime_cr(self, agent_name: str, cr_spec: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n198:     \"\"\"Apply CR using CustomObjectsApi.\"\"\"\n199: \n200:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n201:     \"\"\"Get AgentRuntime CR status.\"\"\"\n202: \n203:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n204:     \"\"\"Delete AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ### Kubernetes Client Initialization Flow\n208: \n209: ```\n210: _get_k8s_client()\n211:     │\n212:     ▼\n213: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n214: │ Check cached client         │\n215: │ (self._k8s_client)          │\n216: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n217:               │ Exists\n218:               ▼\n219:        ┌──────────────┐\n220:        │ Return cached │\n221:        └───────────────┘\n222:               │ Not exists\n223:               ▼\n224: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n225: │ Try import kubernetes       │\n226: │ (client, config)            │\n227: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n228:               │ ImportError\n229:               ▼\n230: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n231: │ Raise RuntimeError          │\n232: │ \"pip install kubernetes\"    │\n233: └─────────────────────────────┘\n234:               │ Success\n235:               ▼\n236: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n237: │ Try load_kube_config()      │\n238: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n239:               │ Success\n240:               ▼\n241:        ┌──────────────┐\n242:        │ Log \"kubeconfig\"│\n243:        └──────┬─────────┘\n244:               │ Failure\n245:               ▼\n246: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n247: │ Try load_incluster_config() │\n248: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n249:               │ Success\n250:               ▼\n251:        ┌──────────────┐\n252:        │ Log \"in-cluster\"│\n253:        └──────┬─────────┘\n254:               │ Failure\n255:               ▼\n256: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n257: │ Raise RuntimeError          │\n258: │ \"Failed to load K8s config\" │\n259: └─────────────────────────────┘\n260:               │\n261:               ▼\n262: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n263: │ Initialize APIs             │\n264: │ - AppsV1Api                 │\n265: │ - CoreV1Api                 │\n266: │ - CustomObjectsApi          │\n267: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n268:               │\n269:               ▼\n270:        ┌──────────────┐\n271:        │ Return client │\n272:        └───────────────┘\n273: ```\n274: \n275: ### Deployment Flow (KubernetesProvider)\n276: \n277: ```\n278: deploy_agent(agent_name, image_url, port, ...)\n279:     │\n280:     ▼\n281: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n282: │ Validate node_port range    │\n283: │ (30000-32767 if provided)   │\n284: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n285:               │ Invalid\n286:               ▼\n287: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n288: │ Raise ValueError            │\n289: └─────────────────────────────┘\n290:               │ Valid\n291:               ▼\n292: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n293: │ _get_k8s_client()           │\n294: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n295:               │\n296:               ▼\n297: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n298: │ _ensure_namespace()         │\n299: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n300:               │\n301:               ▼\n302: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n303: │ _create_or_update_deployment│\n304: │ - Build V1Deployment        │\n305: │ - Try update, catch 404     │\n306: │ - Create if not exists      │\n307: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n308:               │\n309:               ▼\n310: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n311: │ _create_or_update_service   │\n312: │ - Build V1Service (NodePort)│\n313: │ - Try update, catch 404     │\n314: │ - Create if not exists      │\n315: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n316:               │\n317:               ▼\n318: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n319: │ Build result dict           │\n320: │ - deployment_name           │\n321: │ - service_name              │\n322: │ - node_port                 │\n323: │ - service_url               │\n324: │ - status: \"deployed\"        │\n325: └─────────────────────────────┘\n326: ```\n327: \n328: ### AgentRuntime CR Structure\n329: \n330: ```yaml\n331: apiVersion: agentcube.io/v1\n332: kind: AgentRuntime\n333: metadata:\n334:   name: {agent_name}\n335:   namespace: {namespace}\n336: spec:\n337:   image: {image_url}\n338:   port: {port}\n339:   sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n340:   maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n341:   podTemplate:\n342:     spec:\n343:       imagePullSecrets:\n344:         - name: default-secret\n345:       containers:\n346:         - name: {agent_name}\n347:           image: {image_url}\n348:           ports:\n349:             - containerPort: {port}\n350:           env:\n351:             - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n352:               value: {workload_manager_url}\n353:             - name: ROUTER_URL\n354:               value: {router_url}\n355:           command: [{entrypoint_command}]  # if entrypoint provided\n356:           args: [{entrypoint_args}]        # if args exist\n357:           readinessProbe:                  # if readiness_probe_path set\n358:             httpGet:\n359:               path: {readiness_probe_path}\n360:               port: {readiness_probe_port}\n361:             initialDelaySeconds: 10\n362:             periodSeconds: 5\n363: ```\n364: \n365: ---\n366: \n367: ## Impact Analysis\n368: \n369: ### Affected Components\n370: \n371: | Component | Impact | Description |\n372: |-----------|--------|-------------|\n373: | `PublishRuntime` | High | Uses both providers for `publish` command |\n374: | `StatusRuntime` | High | Uses both providers for `status` command |\n375: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Medium | `--provider` flag affects provider selection |\n376: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | High | New file for KubernetesProvider |\n377: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | High | New file for AgentCubeProvider |\n378: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Low | May export provider classes |\n379: | `pyproject.toml` | Low | Optional `kubernetes` dependency |\n380: \n381: ### Deployment Configuration Changes\n382: \n383: **Standard K8s Deployment Result:**\n384: ```python\n385: {\n386:     \"deployment_name\": \"my-agent\",\n387:     \"service_name\": \"my-agent\",\n388:     \"namespace\": \"default\",\n389:     \"node_port\": 30080,\n390:     \"replicas\": 1,\n391:     \"service_url\": \"http://localhost:30080\",\n392:     \"status\": \"deployed\",\n393: }\n394: ```\n395: \n396: **AgentRuntime CR Deployment Result:**\n397: ```python\n398: {\n399:     \"agent_id\": \"my-agent\",\n400:     \"agent_endpoint\": \"http://router:8080/v1/agents/my-agent\",\n401:     \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n402:     \"namespace\": \"default\",\n403:     \"status\": \"deployed\",\n404:     \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n405:     \"router_url\": \"http://router:8080\",\n406: }\n407: ```\n408: \n409: ### Error Scenarios\n410: \n411: | Scenario | Exception | Message Pattern |\n412: |----------|-----------|-----------------|\n413: | K8s library not installed | `RuntimeError` | \"Kubernetes client library not installed\" |\n414: | K8s config load failure | `RuntimeError` | \"Failed to load Kubernetes configuration\" |\n415: | Invalid node_port | `ValueError` | \"NodePort must be in range 30000-32767\" |\n416: | Deployment timeout | `TimeoutError` | \"did not become ready within {timeout} seconds\" |\n417: | Missing AgentCube URLs | `ValueError` | \"requires router_url and workload_manager_url\" |\n418: | Deployment failure | `RuntimeError` | \"Deployment {name} failed: {message}\" |\n419: | CR apply failure | `RuntimeError` | \"Failed to deploy AgentRuntime: {e}\" |\n420: | Resource not found | Returns dict | `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}` |\n421: \n422: ---\n423: \n424: ## Alternatives Considered\n425: \n426: ### Alternative 1: Single Unified Provider\n427: \n428: **Approach**: Combine both providers into a single class with mode flags.\n429: \n430: **Rejected**: Separation of concerns. Standard K8s and AgentRuntime CR have fundamentally different deployment models, configuration requirements, and status checking mechanisms. Keeping them separate allows independent evolution and clearer code organization.\n431: \n432: ### Alternative 2: kubectl CLI Invocation\n433: \n434: **Approach**: Use subprocess to call `kubectl` commands instead of Python kubernetes client.\n435: \n436: **Rejected**: Less efficient, harder to parse results, requires kubectl binary in PATH, less type-safe. Using the official Python client provides better error handling, structured responses, and integrates better with the CLI's Python codebase.\n437: \n438: ### Alternative 3: Helm-based Deployment\n439: \n440: **Approach**: Use Helm charts for deployment instead of direct API calls.\n441: \n442: **Rejected**: Adds Helm as a dependency, overkill for simple deployments, harder to customize per-deployment parameters programmatically. Direct API calls provide more control and fewer external dependencies.\n443: \n444: ### Alternative 4: Kubernetes Operator\n445: \n446: **Approach**: Build a full Kubernetes operator with CRDs and controllers.\n447: \n448: **Rejected**: Too complex for CLI tool requirements. An operator would require cluster-admin setup, separate deployment process, and ongoing maintenance. The current approach uses the existing AgentRuntime CRD without requiring operator installation.\n449: \n450: ### Alternative 5: Server-side Apply Only\n451: \n452: **Approach**: Use only server-side apply (SSA) for all resource updates.\n453: \n454: **Deferred**: While SSA is modern best practice, the client library's support and complexity don't justify the migration for this use case. The current create-or-update pattern is well-understood and reliable.\n455: \n456: ### Alternative 6: Support for Additional Workload Types\n457: \n458: **Approach**: Support DaemonSet, Job, CronJob in addition to Deployment.\n459: \n460: **Rejected**: Out of scope for agent deployment use cases. Agents are long-running services best modeled as Deployments. Can be added later if requirements change.\n461: \n462: ---\n463: \n464: ## Verification\n465: \n466: ### KubernetesProvider Deployment Verification\n467: \n468: ```python\n469: from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n470: \n471: # Initialize provider\n472: provider = KubernetesProvider(namespace=\"default\", verbose=True)\n473: \n474: # Deploy agent\n475: result = provider.deploy_agent(\n476:     agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n477:     image_url=\"nginx:latest\",\n478:     port=8080,\n479:     replicas=2,\n480:     node_port=30080,\n481: )\n482: \n483: print(f\"Deployment: {result['deployment_name']}\")\n484: print(f\"Service URL: {result['service_url']}\")\n485: \n486: # Wait for readiness\n487: try:\n488:     status = provider.wait_for_deployment_ready(\"test-agent\", timeout=120)\n489:     print(f\"Ready: {status['ready_replicas']}/{status['desired_replicas']}\")\n490: except TimeoutError as e:\n491:     print(f\"Timeout: {e}\")\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ### AgentCubeProvider Deployment Verification\n495: \n496: ```python\n497: from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n498: \n499: # Initialize provider\n500: provider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=\"default\", verbose=True)\n501: \n502: # Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n503: result = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n504:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n505:     image_url=\"my-registry/agent:v1.0.0\",\n506:     port=8080,\n507:     workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n508:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n509:     readiness_probe_path=\"/health\",\n510:     session_timeout=\"30m\",\n511: )\n512: \n513: print(f\"Agent ID: {result['agent_id']}\")\n514: print(f\"Endpoint: {result['agent_endpoint']}\")\n515: ```\n516: \n517: ### Status Check Verification\n518: \n519: ```python\n520: # Check K8s provider status\n521: status = provider.get_agent_status(\"test-agent\")\n522: print(f\"Replicas: {status['deployment']['ready_replicas']}/{status['deployment']['replicas']}\")\n523: print(f\"NodePort: {status['service']['node_port']}\")\n524: \n525: # Check AgentCube provider status\n526: status = provider.get_agent_status(\"my-agent\")\n527: print(f\"Status: {status['status']}\")\n528: ```\n529: \n530: ### Cleanup Verification\n531: \n532: ```python\n533: # Delete resources\n534: result = provider.delete_agent(\"test-agent\")\n535: print(f\"Deployment deleted: {result['deployment_deleted']}\")\n536: print(f\"Service deleted: {result['service_deleted']}\")\n537: \n538: # Idempotent delete (no error if not exists)\n539: result = provider.delete_agent(\"non-existent\")\n540: print(f\"Status: {result}\")  # Shows not_found, no exception\n541: ```\n542: \n543: ### Error Handling Verification\n544: \n545: ```python\n546: # Invalid node_port\n547: try:\n548:     provider.deploy_agent(\n549:         agent_name=\"test\",\n550:         image_url=\"nginx:latest\",\n551:         port=8080,\n552:         node_port=1000,  # Invalid range\n553:     )\n554: except ValueError as e:\n555:     print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n556: \n557: # Missing URLs for AgentCube\n558: try:\n559:     agentcube_provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n560:         agent_name=\"test\",\n561:         image_url=\"nginx:latest\",\n562:         port=8080,\n563:         # Missing workload_manager_url and router_url\n564:     )\n565: except ValueError as e:\n566:     print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n567: ```\n568: \n569: ---\n570: \n571: ## References\n572: \n573: - [cli-toolkit/design.md](cli-toolkit/design.md) — CLI package layout and provider architecture\n574: - [cli-toolkit/spec.md](cli-toolkit/spec.md) — Provider requirements specification\n575: - [deployment/client-go.md](deployment/client-go.md) — AgentRuntime CR API specification\n576: - [Kubernetes Python Client Documentation](https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python) — Official Python client docs\n577: - [Kubernetes Deployment Documentation](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/deployment/) — K8s Deployment concepts\n578: - [Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/) — CRD concepts\n579: - AR-020 — CLI Pack Command (precedes publish)\n580: - AR-021 — CLI Build Command (precedes publish)\n581: - AR-022 — CLI Publish Command (uses providers)\n582: - AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Commands (uses providers)\n583: - AR-024 — DockerService Encapsulation (related service pattern)\n584: - AR-025 — MetadataService (provides deployment parameters)\n585: \n586: ---\n587: \n588: ## Success Criteria\n589: \n590: 1. ✅ `KubernetesProvider` class exists in `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n591: 2. ✅ `AgentCubeProvider` class exists in `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n592: 3. ✅ Both providers have `namespace` and `verbose` constructor parameters\n593: 4. ✅ `_get_k8s_client()` implements lazy initialization with config fallback\n594: 5. ✅ `_ensure_namespace()` creates namespace if it doesn't exist\n595: 6. ✅ `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` creates Deployment + NodePort Service\n596: 7. ✅ `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready()` polls with timeout\n597: 8. ✅ `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` returns deployment and service status\n598: 9. ✅ `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent()` removes both resources\n599: 10. ✅ `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` creates AgentRuntime CR\n600: 11. ✅ AgentRuntime CR includes required environment variables (WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, ROUTER_URL)\n601: 12. ✅ AgentRuntime CR includes default imagePullSecrets (`default-secret`)\n602: 13. ✅ Readiness probe is configured when readiness_probe_path is provided\n603: 14. ✅ Session timeout defaults to \"15m\" and max duration to \"8h\"\n604: 15. ✅ `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_status()` returns CR status\n605: 16. ✅ `AgentCubeProvider.delete_agent()` deletes the CR\n606: 17. ✅ Entrypoint parsing correctly splits into command and args\n607: 18. ✅ NodePort validation enforces 30000-32767 range\n608: 19. ✅ Missing AgentCube URLs raise `ValueError` with clear message\n609: 20. ✅ Kubernetes client initialization errors raise `RuntimeError`\n610: 21. ✅ Both providers use structured logging via `self.logger`\n611: 22. ✅ Providers are importable from `agentcube.services`\n612: 23. ✅ NotFoundException during delete is handled gracefully (idempotent)\n613: 24. ✅ Deployment timeout raises `TimeoutError` with descriptive message\n614: \n615: ---\n616: \n617: *AR-026 — Module: cmd/cli — Language: Python — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 617 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n\n## AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes to enable deployment of AI agents to Kubernetes using either standard K8s resources (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube-specific `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR). These providers SHALL serve as the deployment abstraction layer for the AgentCube CLI, enabling seamless publishing of agents to diverse Kubernetes environments.\n\nThe dual-provider architecture SHALL:\n- Support standard Kubernetes deployments for generic K8s clusters\n- Support AgentRuntime CR deployments for AgentCube-enabled clusters","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775901917057,"end":1775901917069}}}}
