{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775902324414,"sessionID":"ses_283ffa16affeyiZ24apvNnRQcH","part":{"id":"prt_d7c01936e00127KTAvMvlJEY6B","messageID":"msg_d7c014480001bvuKv4gdXrWLor","sessionID":"ses_283ffa16affeyiZ24apvNnRQcH","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: SDK CodeInterpreterClient (AR-027)\n\n## AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `sdk-python` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` classes as part of the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) to provide a comprehensive Python client library for interacting with the AgentCube platform. This SDK SHALL enable programmatic creation of Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execution of code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invocation of AgentRuntime workloads.\n\nThe SDK SHALL:\n- Provide a high-level `CodeInterpreterClient` for sandboxed code execution with automatic session lifecycle management\n- Provide an `AgentRuntimeClient` for invoking agent workloads through the Router\n- Support both context manager and explicit lifecycle patterns for resource cleanup\n- Handle authentication via Bearer tokens (environment variable or Kubernetes service account)\n- Implement proper connection pooling and timeout management for HTTP operations\n- Define a clear exception hierarchy for error handling\n- Support file operations (upload, download, write, list) in Code Interpreter sessions\n- Enable multiple programming language execution (Python, JavaScript, Bash) through the Code Interpreter\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **CodeInterpreterClient — High-Level Session Client**\n   - `__init__()` — Initialize with configuration for session name, namespace, TTL, and connection URLs\n   - `_init_data_plane()` — Initialize data plane client with session header\n   - `__enter__()` / `__exit__()` — Context manager support for automatic cleanup\n   - `stop()` — Close data plane session and delete control plane session\n   - `execute_command()` — Execute shell commands in the Code Interpreter sandbox\n   - `run_code()` — Execute code in supported languages (Python, JavaScript, Bash)\n   - `write_file()` — Write text content to files in the sandbox\n   - `upload_file()` — Upload local files to the sandbox\n   - `download_file()` — Download files from the sandbox to local storage\n   - `list_files()` — List files in the sandbox at a given path\n\n2. **AgentRuntimeClient — Agent Workload Client**\n   - `__init__()` — Initialize with agent name, namespace, router URL, and timeout settings\n   - `__enter__()` / `__exit__()` — Context manager support\n   - `invoke()` — POST JSON payloads to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint\n   - `close()` — Explicitly close the underlying HTTP session\n   - Session ID bootstrapping via GET request to invocation endpoint\n\n3. **ControlPlaneClient — Workload Manager Client**\n   - `create_session()` — POST to `/v1/code-interpreter` to create sessions\n   - `delete_session()` — DELETE session by ID with 404 handling\n   - `close()` — Close the HTTP session\n   - Environment-based URL resolution (`WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`)\n   - Service account token file support (`/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`)\n\n4. **CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — Router Client for Code Interpreter**\n   - `execute_command()` — POST to `api/execute` with command and timeout\n   - `run_code()` — Language-specific code execution (writes file then executes)\n   - `write_file()` — POST to `api/files` with base64-encoded content\n   - `upload_file()` — Multipart POST to `api/files`\n   - `download_file()` — GET from `api/files/{path}` with streaming\n   - `list_files()` — GET from `api/files` with query parameter\n   - Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n\n5. **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient — Router Client for Agent Runtime**\n   - `bootstrap_session_id()` — GET invocation base URL to obtain session ID\n   - `invoke()` — POST JSON payload with session header\n   - `close()` — Close HTTP session\n   - Timeout tuple handling `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)`\n\n6. **HTTP Utilities**\n   - `create_session()` — Factory for `requests.Session` with connection pooling\n   - `HTTPAdapter` configuration with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n7. **Exception Hierarchy**\n   - `AgentCubeError` — Base exception class\n   - `CommandExecutionError` — Non-zero exit code with exit_code, stderr, command\n   - `SessionError` — Session creation/management failures (defined for extension)\n   - `DataPlaneError` — Data plane operation failures (defined for extension)\n\n8. **Utility Functions**\n   - `read_token_from_file()` — Read and strip token file contents\n   - `get_logger()` — Structured logging with configurable level\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n1. **WebSocket Real-Time Streaming**: No WebSocket support for live output streaming (separate AR)\n2. **AsyncIO Support**: Synchronous API only; async variants not included\n3. **Multi-Region Load Balancing**: Single router URL per client instance\n4. **Client-Side Caching**: No response caching mechanism\n5. **CLI Interface**: SDK is library-only; no command-line interface\n6. **TypeScript/JavaScript SDK**: Python-only implementation\n7. **Custom HTTP Adapters**: Standard requests library usage only\n8. **Connection Retry Logic**: Basic requests retry handling only\n9. **Response Schema Validation**: JSON parsing without Pydantic models\n10. **Metrics and Telemetry**: No built-in metrics collection\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### SDK Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    agentcube (Public API)                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  CodeInterpreterClient        │  AgentRuntimeClient             │\n│  - Session lifecycle          │  - Invoke workloads             │\n│  - Code execution             │  - Session bootstrap            │\n│  - File operations            │  - Payload posting              │\n└───────────────┬───────────────────────────────┬─────────────────┘\n                │                               │\n    ┌───────────┴───────────┐       ┌───────────┴───────────┐\n    ▼                       ▼       ▼                       ▼\n┌─────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n│ ControlPlane    │  │ CodeInterpreterData  │  │ AgentRuntimeData │\n│ Client          │  │ PlaneClient          │  │ PlaneClient      │\n├─────────────────┤  ├──────────────────────┤  ├──────────────────┤\n│ create_session  │  │ execute_command      │  │ bootstrap_session│\n│ delete_session  │  │ run_code             │  │ invoke           │\n│ close           │  │ write_file           │  │ close            │\n└────────┬────────┘  │ upload_file          │  └────────┬─────────┘\n         │           │ download_file        │           │\n         │           │ list_files           │           │\n         │           └──────────┬───────────┘           │\n         │                      │                       │\n         └──────────────────────┼───────────────────────┘\n                                │\n                    ┌───────────┴───────────┐\n                    ▼                       ▼\n            ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n            │  create_session │     │  read_token_    │\n            │  (HTTP utility) │     │  from_file      │\n            └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreterClient Lifecycle\n\n```\n__init__(name, namespace, ttl, workload_manager_url, router_url, ...)\n    │\n    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Validate router_url         │\n│ (arg or ROUTER_URL env)     │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ Not provided\n              ▼\n       ┌──────────────┐\n       │ Raise Value  │\n       │ Error        │\n       └──────────────┘\n              │ Provided\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Initialize ControlPlane     │\n│ Client                      │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ session_id provided?        │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ No\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ create_session()            │\n│ POST /v1/code-interpreter   │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ _init_data_plane()          │\n│ (may raise)                 │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ Raises\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Log warning                 │\n│ delete_session()            │\n│ session_id = None           │\n│ Re-raise                    │\n└─────────────────────────────┘\n              │ Success\n              ▼\n       ┌──────────────┐\n       │ Ready for    │\n       │ operations   │\n       └──────────────┘\n```\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient Lifecycle\n\n```\n__init__(agent_name, namespace, router_url, ...)\n    │\n    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ session_id provided?        │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ No\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ GET {router}/v1/namespaces/ │\n│ {ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/ │\n│ invocations/                │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Read x-agentcube-session-id │\n│ response header             │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ Missing\n              ▼\n       ┌──────────────┐\n       │ Raise Value  │\n       │ Error        │\n       └──────────────┘\n              │ Present\n              ▼\n       ┌──────────────┐\n       │ Initialize   │\n       │ dp_client    │\n       └──────────────┘\n```\n\n### Class Structure\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize Code Interpreter client with session configuration.\"\"\"\n\n    def _init_data_plane(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize data plane client with session header.\"\"\"\n\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\": ...\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Context manager exit - calls stop().\"\"\"\n\n    def stop(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close data plane, delete control plane session, close HTTP sessions.\"\"\"\n\n    def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Execute shell command in sandbox; raises CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit.\"\"\"\n\n    def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Execute code in specified language (python, javascript, bash).\"\"\"\n\n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Write text content to file in sandbox.\"\"\"\n\n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Upload local file to sandbox via multipart POST.\"\"\"\n\n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Download file from sandbox to local path.\"\"\"\n\n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n        \"\"\"List files in sandbox at given path.\"\"\"\n```\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize Agent Runtime client.\"\"\"\n\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\": ...\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Context manager exit - calls close().\"\"\"\n\n    def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any:\n        \"\"\"POST payload to Agent Runtime invocation endpoint.\"\"\"\n\n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close underlying HTTP session.\"\"\"\n```\n\n#### ControlPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize Workload Manager control plane client.\"\"\"\n\n    def create_session(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Create session and return session_id.\"\"\"\n\n    def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Delete session; returns True (404 treated as success).\"\"\"\n\n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close HTTP session.\"\"\"\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n        cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n        base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize data plane client for Code Interpreter.\"\"\"\n\n    def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response:\n        \"\"\"Internal request with session header.\"\"\"\n\n    def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n    def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### HTTP Endpoint Mapping\n\n#### Control Plane (Workload Manager)\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `/v1/code-interpreter` | Create session with name, namespace, ttl, metadata |\n| `DELETE` | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | Delete session (404 = success) |\n\n**Headers:**\n- `Content-Type: application/json`\n- `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token resolved)\n\n#### Data Plane — Code Interpreter (Router)\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Body/Params | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `api/execute` | `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` | Execute command |\n| `POST` | `api/files` | `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` | Write file |\n| `POST` | `api/files` | `files={'file': ...}, data={'path', 'mode'}` | Upload file (multipart) |\n| `GET` | `api/files/{path}` | `stream=True` | Download file |\n| `GET` | `api/files` | `?path={path}` | List files |\n\n**Headers:**\n- `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (all requests)\n- `Content-Type: application/json` (JSON requests)\n\n#### Data Plane — Agent Runtime (Router)\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Headers | Body |\n|--------|----------|---------|------|\n| `GET` | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/` | — | — |\n| `POST` | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```\nException\n└── AgentCubeError (agentcube.exceptions)\n    ├── CommandExecutionError\n    │   ├── exit_code: int\n    │   ├── stderr: str\n    │   └── command: Optional[str]\n    ├── SessionError (for extension)\n    └── DataPlaneError (for extension)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Affected Components\n\n| Component | Impact | Description |\n|-----------|--------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | High | New file for CodeInterpreterClient |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | High | New file for AgentRuntimeClient |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | High | New file for ControlPlaneClient |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | High | New file for CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | High | New file for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient |\n| `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Medium | Re-export client classes |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Medium | Export CodeInterpreterClient and AgentRuntimeClient |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | High | New file for exception hierarchy |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Medium | New file for create_session utility |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Low | New file for read_token_from_file |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Low | New file for get_logger |\n| `pyproject.toml` | Low | Package dependencies and metadata |\n| `examples/basic_usage.py` | Low | Example CodeInterpreterClient usage |\n| `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py` | Low | Example AgentRuntimeClient usage |\n\n### Package Dependencies\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n```\n\n### Configuration Resolution\n\n| Setting | Environment Variable | Default |\n|---------|---------------------|---------|\n| `router_url` | `ROUTER_URL` | Required (ValueError if missing) |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | `None` |\n| `auth_token` | Service account token file | `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n| `timeout` | — | `120` seconds |\n| `connect_timeout` | — | `5.0` seconds |\n\n### Timeout Behavior\n\n| Operation | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout |\n|-----------|-----------------|--------------|\n| Control plane calls | `5.0s` | `120s` |\n| Data plane execute | `5.0s` | `timeout + 2.0s` (buffer) |\n| Data plane files | `5.0s` | `120s` |\n| Agent Runtime invoke | `5.0s` | `self.timeout` (default 120s) |\n\n### Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Exception | Message Pattern |\n|----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| Missing router_url | `ValueError` | Router URL must be provided |\n| Missing session header | `ValueError` | Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id |\n| Command non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError` | Command failed (exit {code}): {stderr} |\n| Missing session_id for invoke | `ValueError` | AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized |\n| Session create without sessionId | `ValueError` | Session ID not found in response |\n| Data plane init failure | Warning logged, session deleted, re-raised | — |\n| Delete session 404 | Returns `True` (idempotent) | — |\n| Delete session other error | Returns `False`, logged | — |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Single Client Class\n\n**Approach**: Combine CodeInterpreterClient and AgentRuntimeClient into a single unified client with mode flags.\n\n**Rejected**: Different use cases and API patterns. Code Interpreter focuses on session-based sandboxed execution with file operations, while Agent Runtime focuses on stateless payload invocation. Keeping them separate provides clearer APIs and independent evolution paths.\n\n### Alternative 2: AsyncIO-First Design\n\n**Approach**: Build the SDK with `async`/`await` and `aiohttp` as the primary interface.\n\n**Rejected**: Adds complexity for the majority of use cases that don't need concurrent operations. The synchronous `requests`-based design is simpler and more familiar to Python developers. Async support can be added later as a separate async client module.\n\n### Alternative 3: Pydantic Models for Validation\n\n**Approach**: Use Pydantic for request/response validation and serialization.\n\n**Rejected**: Adds a heavy dependency for relatively simple data structures. The SDK uses standard Python dictionaries and type hints, keeping dependencies minimal (requests, PyJWT, cryptography only).\n\n### Alternative 4: Auto-Generated Client from OpenAPI\n\n**Approach**: Generate the SDK client from an OpenAPI specification using tools like openapi-generator.\n\n**Rejected**: Generated clients often have poor ergonomics and don't match the desired high-level API design. A hand-crafted client provides better control over the user experience and can handle SDK-specific concerns like session lifecycle management.\n\n### Alternative 5: Unified Configuration Class\n\n**Approach**: Create a single `Configuration` dataclass to hold all settings.\n\n**Rejected**: The distributed configuration approach is more flexible. Different clients have different configuration needs, and environment-based resolution is handled at the appropriate level. This avoids passing unnecessary configuration through multiple layers.\n\n### Alternative 6: Retry Logic with Tenacity\n\n**Approach**: Use the `tenacity` library for sophisticated retry logic with exponential backoff.\n\n**Rejected**: Adds another dependency for functionality that `requests` handles adequately at the adapter level. Retries can be added at the application layer if needed. The SDK keeps dependencies minimal.\n\n### Alternative 7: httpx Instead of requests\n\n**Approach**: Use `httpx` instead of `requests` for both sync and async support in one library.\n\n**Rejected**: While `httpx` is modern and supports both sync/async, `requests` is more widely used and familiar. The SDK prioritizes familiarity and stability over bleeding-edge features. Migration to `httpx` is possible in the future if needed.\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### CodeInterpreterClient Usage Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\n# Context manager with automatic cleanup\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(\n    name=\"my-session\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n) as client:\n    # Execute a command\n    output = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\", timeout=30.0)\n    print(output)\n\n    # Run Python code\n    result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"\"\"\nimport sys\nprint(f\"Python version: {sys.version}\")\n    \"\"\", timeout=60.0)\n    print(result)\n\n    # Write and read files\n    client.write_file(\"Hello, World!\", \"/tmp/hello.txt\")\n    client.download_file(\"/tmp/hello.txt\", \"./local_hello.txt\")\n    files = client.list_files(\"/tmp\")\n    print(files)\n\n# Session automatically cleaned up on exit\n```\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient Usage Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n# Context manager with automatic session bootstrap\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n) as client:\n    # Invoke the agent\n    response = client.invoke({\n        \"message\": \"Hello, Agent!\",\n        \"context\": {\"user_id\": \"123\"}\n    }, timeout=30.0)\n    print(response)\n\n# Session automatically closed on exit\n```\n\n### Error Handling Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n) as client:\n    try:\n        # This will raise CommandExecutionError\n        client.execute_command(\"exit 1\")\n    except CommandExecutionError as e:\n        print(f\"Exit code: {e.exit_code}\")\n        print(f\"Stderr: {e.stderr}\")\n        print(f\"Command: {e.command}\")\n```\n\n### Direct Client Usage Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n# Manual session management\ncp = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\")\nsession_id = cp.create_session(name=\"manual-session\", namespace=\"default\")\nprint(f\"Session: {session_id}\")\n\n# Use data plane directly\ndp = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n    session_id=session_id,\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    cr_name=\"my-interpreter\",\n)\noutput = dp.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\nprint(output)\n\n# Cleanup\ndp.close()\ncp.delete_session(session_id)\ncp.close()\n```\n\n### Environment Configuration Verification\n\n```python\nimport os\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\n# Configure via environment\nos.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"] = \"http://router:8080\"\nos.environ[\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"] = \"http://workload-manager:8080\"\n\n# No URL arguments needed - resolved from environment\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"env-session\") as client:\n    output = client.execute_command(\"whoami\")\n    print(output)\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [python-sdk/design.md](python-sdk/design.md) — SDK package layout and class design\n- [python-sdk/spec.md](python-sdk/spec.md) — SDK requirements specification\n- [session-routing/design.md](session-routing/design.md) — Router API design\n- [sandbox-orchestration/design.md](sandbox-orchestration/design.md) — Workload Manager API design\n- [code-execution/design.md](code-execution/design.md) — Code execution service design\n- [requests Documentation](https://docs.python-requests.org/) — HTTP library\n- [Python Type Hints](https://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html) — Type annotation reference\n- AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider (uses SDK for deployment verification)\n- AR-022 — CLI Publish Command (can use SDK for agent testing)\n- AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Commands (complementary functionality)\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `CodeInterpreterClient` class exists in `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n2. ✅ `AgentRuntimeClient` class exists in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n3. ✅ `ControlPlaneClient` class exists in `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n4. ✅ `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` class exists in `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n5. ✅ `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class exists in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n6. ✅ Exception hierarchy defined in `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n7. ✅ `agentcube/__init__.py` exports `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`\n8. ✅ `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` re-exports all client classes\n9. ✅ Context manager support (`__enter__`, `__exit__`) for both clients\n10. ✅ `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()` closes data plane and deletes control plane session\n11. ✅ `execute_command()` raises `CommandExecutionError` on non-zero exit\n12. ✅ `run_code()` writes timestamped file and executes for Python code\n13. ✅ File operations (`write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`) work correctly\n14. ✅ `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` POSTs JSON with session header\n15. ✅ Session ID bootstrapping via GET request when not provided\n16. ✅ Missing `router_url` raises `ValueError` with clear message\n17. ✅ Missing session header in bootstrap raises `ValueError`\n18. ✅ `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` returns session_id from response\n19. ✅ `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` treats 404 as success\n20. ✅ Service account token file reading works for Kubernetes environments\n21. ✅ Connection pooling configured with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n22. ✅ Timeout defaults: `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n23. ✅ `x-agentcube-session-id` header included on all data plane requests\n24. ✅ Data plane init failure after session create logs warning, deletes session, re-raises\n\n---\n\n*AR-027 — Module: sdk-python — Language: Python — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775902324181,"end":1775902324408}}}}
